<br>
Understandably, this is a major shock to anyone, to be plucked from the field, and into a barrel to be shipped off to defend everything you've had the PLEASURE and RIGHT to attain and enjoy.   I agree with everyone who is afraid of being drafted, <br>
hell it scares me a bit, and I signed up for the Marines back in 96 when I turned 18, and ended up blowing my right knee a month before I would have went to boot camp.  There is a bit of difference in choosing to serve, and being forced to serve.<br>
<br>
My grandfather served in all 4 branches of the military, served in WWII was part of it from the beach of normandy.  He's got medals and what not for his actions an such, and once he told me he'd do it again if he had the chance.   My uncle served in vietnam as well, but he's not open to talk about it, even tho most of the things he's done is declassified now, its just something he'd rather not bring up.  <br>
<br>
Anyway it goes, my knee is better now, I know I can handle boot camp and going to war if I have to.  Like others, I'd rather not, but if drafted, yeah I'll tremble a bit, because I'm being forced into a completely new environment.  Its a life change, so yeah its scarey.  <br>
